ZH: 他在吸烟的时候不小心把裤子烧着了。
EN: He accidentally set his pants on fire while smoking.

ZH: 我们不允许在室内吸烟。
EN: We do not allow smoking indoors.

ZH: 爸爸戒烟已经半年了。
EN: Dad has quit smoking for half a year now.

ZH: 为了保护环境，我们应该减少吸塑料吸管的使用。
EN: To protect the environment, we should reduce the use of plastic straws.

ZH: 请勿在公共场所吸烟。
EN: Please do not smoke in public places.

ZH: 吸毒是非常危险和不良的行为。
EN: Drug use is a very dangerous and harmful behavior.

ZH: 她吸了一口烟，然后把烟蒂扔到了垃圾桶里。
EN: She took a puff of smoke and then threw the cigarette butt into the bin.

ZH: 老板不允许在办公室内吸烟。
EN: The boss does not allow smoking in the office.

ZH: 烟囱排出的尾气对环境造成了很大的影响。
EN: The emissions from the chimney have a great impact on the environment.

ZH: 这个城市正在加强吸烟区域的管理。
EN: The city is strengthening the management of smoking areas.

ZH: 她很伤心，只好一个人在阳台上吸了一支烟。
EN: She was very sad and had to smoke a cigarette alone on the balcony.

ZH: 别吸了，对身体不好。
EN: Don't smoke, it's bad for your health.

ZH: 这个病人禁得了病却受不了戒烟。
EN: This patient can cope with the illness but cannot quit smoking.

ZH: 他吸得特别利索，看来已经练倒了。
EN: He smokes very skillfully, it seems he has practiced a lot.

ZH: 为了给自己一个拥抱，他抽了一根烟。
EN: To give himself a hug, he lit a cigarette.

ZH: 吸烟会对自己的家人造成伤害。
EN: Smoking can harm one's own family members.

ZH: 他的牙齿被吸烟影响得很严重。
EN: His teeth are seriously affected by smoking.

ZH: 不要吸毒，这会毁了你的人生。
EN: Do not do drugs, it will ruin your life.

ZH: 许多人开始吸烟都是受到周围人的影响。
EN: Many people start smoking because they are influenced by people around them.
